HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 305
BY REPRESENTATIVE KNOX
COMMENDATIONS: Commends Chris Hannah for his contributions to the American bar
industry and North American cocktail culture
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend Chris Hannah for his contributions to the American bar industry and North
3 American cocktail culture.
4 WHEREAS, Chris Hannah is based in New Orleans, a city synonymous with the
5 birthplace of the cocktail, and is one of the defining figures of modern American cocktail
6 culture; and
7 WHEREAS, Chris is a bartender whose influence is rooted in precision, restraint, and
8 deep historical knowledge, and he has spent more than two decades refining a style that
9 honors tradition while maintaining a quietly contemporary quality; and
10 WHEREAS, Chris had humble beginnings in the hospitality sector; he worked as a
11 dishwasher at Locke's Point, a bar in North Carolina, and subsequently spent six years doing
12 line work; and
13 WHEREAS, Chris rose to prominence at the French 75 Bar inside Arnaud's, where
14 he helped transform the bar into a national benchmark for classic cocktail execution; the bar
15 earned a James Beard Foundation Award for Outstanding Bar Program during his tenure,
16 which cemented his reputation as a leading force in the cocktail industry; and
17 WHEREAS, Chris's work at the French 75 Bar was defined by his unwavering
18 commitment to balance, technique, and hospitality, qualities that have become hallmarks of
19 his career; and
20 WHEREAS, Chris's bartending philosophy focuses on the revival and refinement of
21 historic drinks while maintaining the integrity of icons like the sazerac and French 75; and
